
If your project doesn't have a specific root folder and you are working directly in the root directory (i.e., everything is in the same directory), you can simplify the vercel.json file accordingly.

Hereâ€™s the updated configuration assuming:

Your index.js (backend) is in the root folder.
Your build output (Vite) is in the dist folder.
Updated vercel.json:
json
Copy code
{
  "version": 2,
  "builds": [
    {
      "src": "index.js",
      "use": "@vercel/node"
    },
    {
      "src": "dist/**/*",
      "use": "@vercel/static"
    }
  ],
  "routes": [
    {
      "src": "/(.*)",
      "dest": "/dist/$1"
    },
    {
      "src": "/api/(.*)",
      "dest": "/index.js"
    }
  ]
}